---
description: Branch naming convention for issue-driven work
alwaysApply: true
---

## Branch naming

New working branches MUST follow this format:

```text
<coder>/<issue-id>-<short-description>
```

## Rules

- Use lowercase only.
- Use kebab-case for description.
- Keep description short and intent-focused.
- `coder` should identify person or team namespace owning branch.
- `issue-id` should match tracker identifier for work item linked to branch.
- Reference exactly one issue per branch when branch is issue-driven.

## Examples

- `ailuracodedev/alp-13-add-mcp-server-configuration`
- `pabloguerra/alp-21-fix-theme-storage-event`
- `frontend/team-144-improve-dialog-focus-handling`

## Do not

- Do not use spaces, uppercase letters, or underscores.
- Do not create generic names like `fix/bug`, `feature/test`, or `wip`.
- Do not mix multiple issues in one branch.
